locality: Wichupurhua - - Leaving Aguilani to walk to Choquetanga the trail climbs straight up to the ridge of the Serrania de Lulini. Following the ridge ca 1 km one comes to a small permanent lake, the only free water in this area. The lake is called Wichu Purhua. It is 3 km due S. of the actual site of Aguilani (which is misplaced on maps) and 13.5 km N. of Choquetanga.
6 km (by air) SE of Inquisivi, Machacamarca
Alrededores de Huamachuco, borde de carretera.

Cerro Aguada - - On this day we climbed from the junction of the Río Aquada and Río Mikhailpurhua (3.5 km NNE from the mouth of the Río Aguilani at Lakachaka) to near the summit of Cerro Aguada about 5 km SSW from Communidad Khora. 24 km N. of Choquetanga. Habitats as follows: 1800-2500 m burned grasslands with serious erosion, 2500-2800 m fern heath, mattoral and Alnus dominated woodlands, seriously intervened and burned, 2800-3000 m Alnus domminated woodlands with some high cloud forest species.
Trujillo-Huamachuco road, about 10km W of Huamachuco. Ravines and hedgerows in agricultural area, the natural vegetation heavily disturbed by centuries of civilization.
Machupicchu, a 107 km de Cusco. Bosque de ceja de selva entre Wiñayhuayna e Intipunco; presencia de Clethra, Podocarpus y Alnus.
Valley of Río Marcará, below Vicos 2-3 km.
Near Curupampa on the road from Achacachi to Sorata
6 km de Sorata, camino a Consata..
La Paz: Inquisivi. Walk along the road between the Rio Poqueloque (Huarctolo turnoff) and Entre Rios. Ca. 8-12 km N from Licoma Pampa.
